{{Infobox language |name=Hijra Farsi |nativename=فارسی چانڈڑنہ |state=[[India]], [[Pakistan]] |speakers=Unknown (0) |date= 2017 |familycolor=Indo-European |fam2=[[Indo-Iranian languages|Indo-Iranian]] |fam3=[[Indo-Aryan languages|Indo-Aryan]] |fam4=[[Hindi languages|Central Zone (Hindi)]] |fam5=[[Western Hindi]] |fam6=[[Hindustani language|Hindustani]]<ref name=ELL2>{{ELL2|Hindustani}}</ref> |fam7=[[Khariboli dialect|Khariboli]]<ref name=ELL2/> |fam8=[[Urdu]] |script=[[Urdu alphabet]], [[Devanagari]] |iso3=none |glotto=none }} '''Hijra Farsi''' (Urdu: {{urd|فارسی چانڈڑنہ}}) is a [[Cant (language)|secret language]] spoken by South-Asian [[Hijra (South Asia)|hijra]] and [[Kothi (gender)|koti]] communities. Hijras are a marginalized [[transgender]] community that lives in sequestered groups in many cities of India and Pakistan. The language, also known as ''Koti Farsi'', is spoken by the hijra community throughout Pakistan and North India (except [[West Bengal]]). The language is based on [[Hindustani language|Hindustani]] and not [[Persian language|Farsi]], as suggested by the name.<ref name=Hall2001>{{cite web|url=http://www.stanford.edu/dept/linguistics/colloq/prev/2001/2001feb09.html|title=Stanford Linguistics Colloquium|work=stanford.edu|accessdate=16 February 2016}}</ref> The sentence structure is similar to [[Urdu]], but noticeable distinctions exist.<ref>Sheeraz, Muhammad, and Ayaz Afsar. "Farsi: An Invisible But Loaded Weapon for the Emerging Hijraism in Pakistan." Kashmir Journal of Language Research 14, no. 2 (2011).</ref> Even though the language is not actually based on Persian (Farsi), the hijras consider the language to be related to the language of the [[Mughal Empire]], which they associate with the origin of hijra identity. Hijra Farsi is most similar to Hindi, but is not intelligible to Hindi speakers due to distinctive intonation and a large amount of distinctive vocabulary.<ref name=Hall2001/>
After the partition of India, the language has come to include words of local languages including [[Punjabi language|Punjabi]], [[Saraiki language|Saraiki]], [[Sindhi language|Sindhi]] and other languages. ==Comparison== {| class="wikitable sortable" |- ! HF !! UR !! EN |- | کھومبڑ || چہرا || Face |- | کھومڑ || چہرے || Faces |- | janani || زانانہ || |- | Janana || مردانہ || Effeminate |- | Jovan || نوجوان|| Youthfulness |- | Koti || تہے || Bottom |- | Satla || || |- | Panthi/Giriya ||انچا || Top |- | unknown || رس || Juice |- |}
